tus=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Isis (band)|Isis]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://heavymetal.about.com/od/cdreviews/fr/isisintheabsenc.htm|title=Reviews|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://altpress.com/reviews/430.htm |title=''In the Absence of Truth'' review at Altpress |access-date=2007-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809210810/http://www.altpress.com/reviews/430.htm |archive-date=2011-08-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"bandcamp\"/>\n\n'''J'''\n* [[Jesu (band)|Jesu]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Jurek|first=Thom|title=Heart Ache/Dethroned \u2013 Jesu|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/heart-achedethroned-r2049023/review|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=29 December 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"bandcamp\"/>\n*[[Junius (band)|Junius]]<ref>Geist, Brandon. [https://www.rollingstone.com/music/premieres/hear-junius-crushing-new-post-metal-epic-w463118 \"Junius \u2013 The Queen's Constellation\"]. Rolling Stone. Retrieved 27 January 2017.</ref>\n\n'''M'''\n* [[Made Out of Babies]]<ref>True, Chris. [http://www.allmusic.com/artist/made-out-of-babies-p724740 \"Made Out of Babies biography\"]. [[Allmusic]]. Retrieved 27 November 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.skinnymag.co.uk/content/view/3061/141/ Review of ''Red Sparowes / Made Out of Babies / Battle of Mice''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071213233107/http://www.skinnymag.co.uk/content/view/3061/141/ |date=13 December 2007 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.deafsparrow.com/Made-Out-ofBabies-review.htm \"Made Out of Babies \u2013 The Ruiner review \u2013 Deaf Sparrow Zine\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120614182931/http://www.deafsparrow.com/Made-Out-ofBabies-review.htm |date=14 June 2012 }}. deafsparrow.com. Retrieved 1 December 2011.</ref>\n* [[Melvins]]<ref name=\"bandcamp\"/>\n* [[Mouth of the Architect]]<ref>[{{AllMusic|class=album|id=r849391|pure_url=yes}} ''The Ties That Blind'' review at AllMusic]</ref>\n\n'''N'''\n* [[Neurosis (band)|Neurosis]]<ref name=\"bandcamp\"/>\n* [[Nadja (band)|Nadja]]<ref>True, Chris. [http://www.allmusic.com/artist/nadja-p741872 \"Nadja\"]. [[AllMusic]]. Retrieved 28 November 2011.</ref>\n\n'''O'''\n* [[Oathbreaker (band)|Oathbreaker]]<ref name=\"CoS\" />\n* [[The Ocean (band)|The Ocean]]<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=fluxion-r907618/review|pure_url=yes}}|title=Review of Fluxion|last=Freeman|first=Phil|work=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=14 November 2010|quote=The Ocean, a largely Berlin-based musical collective, occupy a space right near Neurosis, Isis, and Cult of Luna in the post-metal arena.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/april-2010,40102/|title=At the Post|last=Pierce|first=Leonard|date=14 April 2010|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|accessdate=14 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n'''P'''\n* [[Pelican (band)|Pelican]]<ref>Jurek, Thom. [http://www.allmusic.com/album/what-we-all-come-to-need-r1663003/review \"Allmusic review: Pelican \u2013 What We All Come to Need\"]. [[AllMusic]]. Retrieved 27 November 2011.</ref><ref name=\"canoe\">{{cite news | url = http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/2006/06/14/1631268.html | archive-url = https://archive.is/20120709090408/http://jam.canoe.ca/Music/2006/06/14/1631268.html | url-status = dead | archive-date = 9 July 2012 | title = Pelican's music tough to categorize | first = Allan | last = Wigley | newspaper = [[Ottawa Sun]] | date = 14 June 2006 | accessdate = 2 August 2007 }}</ref><ref name=\"bandcamp\"/>\n* [[Prong (band)|Prong]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Ramirez|first=Carlos|title=Prong Keep Things Lean and Mean on 'Ammunition' \u2013 Song Premiere|url=http://www.noisecreep.com/2012/04/11/prong-ammunition-song/|work=[[Noisecreep]]|publisher=[[AOL]]|accessdate=19 April 2012|date=11 April 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Palms (band)|Palms]]<ref>Weingarten, Christopher R. [http://www.spin.com/2013/06/stream-palms-debut-chino-moreno-isis-deftones/]. [[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] Retrieved 2 October 2015.</ref>\n\n'''R'''\n* [[Russian Circles]]<ref name=\"steff\" />\n* [[Rosetta (band)|Rosetta]]{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n'''T'''\n* [[Tool (band)|Tool]]<ref name=\"fenix\">{{cite magazine | url = http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117905701.html?categoryid=34&cs=1 | title = Live Performances: Tool | first = Troy J. | last = Augusto | magazine = [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | date = 16 October 1996 | accessdate = 9 May 2007 | quote = The group's rhythm section, featuring new bassist Justin Chancellor, propelled the group's post-metal stylings with a twisted, near-jazz approach.}}</ref><ref name=\"bairdcole\">{{cite news | url = http://www.denverpost.com/entertainment/ci_4298028 | title = Reverb, 9/01: Tool | first = Ricardo | last = Baca | newspaper = [[The Denver Post]] | date = 8 September 2006 | accessdate = 9 May 2007 | quote = ... Tool's bag of post-metal goodies, and it's every bit as fear-inducing as it was in 1993.}}</ref>\n* [[True Widow]]<ref name=\"bandcamp\"/>\n\n'''U'''\n* [[Ulcerate]]<ref>{{cite journal|last=Horsley|first=Jonathan|date=March 2011|title=Kiwi death merchants destroy 'em all|journal=[[Decibel (magazine)|Decibel]]|issue=77|pages=32|issn=1557-2137|quote=What could be better than some evocatively bleak [[death metal]] while panic-buying canned goods and bottled water on the day when the chemical factory has turned the sky green and the river purple? New rager ''[[The Destroyers of All]]'' is a disorienting, desolate doozy, taking elements of weird post-metal to construct a sound that would be mother's milk to [[Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder|ADHD]] [[Neurosis (band)|Neurosis]] fans.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Everything Is Fire review|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/everything-is-fire-r1508696/review|first=Phil|last=Freeman|accessdate=24 April 2011|work=[[Allmusic]]|quote=Their music combines the brutal, downtuned riffing of traditional death metal (think [[Immolation (band)|Immolation]] or [[Morbid Angel]]) with the dissonance and shifting time signatures of [[Gorguts]] and the slow, atmospheric passages reminiscent of [[Isis (band)|Isis]].}}</ref>\n\n'''W'''\n* [[We Lost the Sea]]{{citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n* [[Wolves in the Throne Room]]<ref name=\"bandcamp\"/>\n\n'''Y'''\n* [[Year of No Light]]<ref>[http://www.allmusic.com/artist/year-of-no-light-mn0000525681/biography]. AllMusic.com</ref><ref name=\"bandcamp\"/>\n}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Avant-garde metal]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Heavymetal}}\n{{Experimental music genres}}\n{{Extreme metal}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Post-Metal}}\n[[Category:Post-metal| ]]\n[[Category:Heavy metal genres]]\n[[Category:Experimental music genres]]\n[[Category:Avant-garde metal]]\n[[Category:Experimental rock]]\n[[Category:Post-rock]]\n[[Category:American styles of music]]\n[[Category:American rock music genres]]\n[[Category:English styles of music]]\n[[Category:British rock music genres]]\n", "name_user": "HWT2103", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Post-metal"}
